Down load:
	Piglit is a collection of automated tests for OpenGL implementations.
	The goal of Piglit is to help improve the quality of open source OpenGL drivers by providing developers with a simple means to perform regression tests.
	You can download it from:
	git://anongit.freedesktop.org/git/piglit
 	ssh://git.freedesktop.org/git/piglit
package dependency:
	First of all, you need to make sure that the following are installed:
	- Python 2.4 or greater
	- cmake (http://www.cmake.org)
	- GL, glu and glut libraries and development packages (i.e. headers)
	- X11 libraries and development packages (i.e. headers)
	- libpng, libtiff and related development packages (i.e. headers)

build:
	1. Put piglit under mcts-piglit-tests dir.
	2. Run "pack.sh" to create mcts-piglit-tests-xxx.rpm package
	3. Install the mcts-piglit-tests packages by "rpm -ivh mcts-piglit-tests-xxx.rpm"
run:
	You can choose each of following test scenario.
	1. Run all the cases once:
		testrunner-lite -f tests.xml -o results.xml
	2. Run cases one by one
		testrunner-lite -f tests-asm-ARBfp1.0.xml   -o results.xml
	 	testrunner-lite -f tests-asm-ARBvp1.0.xml   -o results.xml
		testrunner-lite -f tests-bugs.xml   -o results.xml
		testrunner-lite -f tests-fbo.xml   -o results.xml
		testrunner-lite -f tests-general.xml   -o results.xml
		testrunner-lite -f tests-glslparsertest.xml   -o results.xml
		testrunner-lite -f tests-glx.xml   -o results.xml
		testrunner-lite -f tests-shaders.xml   -o results.xml
		testrunner-lite -f tests-texture.xml -o results.xml
note:
	Because Piglit is used for OpenGL API test, So It's OK to be run without WM.
	Just "xinit" then run the cases.

